    "forceCurrentProject": "",
    "summary": "1,600 farmers to be reached",
    "description": "Coffee farmers in Colombia are challenged by low productivity, prices that are lower than costs, and thus low incomes due to a combination of poor fertilizer use, lack of proper soil analysis, along with poor management of pests and diseases. Through this project with Louis Dreyfus Company in the country’s Risaralda, Cauca, Tolima, and Huila regions, we are working to increase the resources and knowledge of farmers related to good agricultural practices, decrease production costs to reduce exposure to price volatility, facilitate access and education of proper inputs, and decrease pollution from water sources. Leveraging a community-level approach, project implementors will motivate farmers, organize the clusters and training activities under the agronomists’ guidance, as well as running demonstration farms.",
