    "id": "water",
    "text": "Coffee farming in southern Sumatra is not a water-intensive activity. With 150–200 rainy days per year, Sumatran farmers rely on rainfall to water their crops and do not irrigate their farms. Also, as most farmers use natural (dry) processing methods, water is rarely used in processing.",
    "riskColor": "#2f75b5"
